killed tradespeople high."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the financial services industry like in Tampa?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Major. Tampa is home to Raymond James Financial headquarters and has large operations for USAA, JPMorgan Chase, Citigroup, and numerous insurance companies. The financial services sector provides well-paying jobs in banking, insurance, wealth management, and fintech. It's one of Tampa's economic pillars and a big reason professionals relocate here."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the job market in St. Petersburg compared to Tampa?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"St. Pete has a growing job market with particular strength in creative industries, healthcare (Johns Hopkins All Children's Hospital), and small business. Tampa has more corporate headquarters and larger employers. Many people live in one city and work in the other — the markets are connected. St. Pete's downtown has attracted startups and creative professionals."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there remote work hubs or coworking spaces in Tampa Bay?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Plenty. Spaces like Industrious, Regus, Novel Coworking, and local options like Station House in St. Pete cater to remote workers and freelancers. Many coffee shops and libraries also serve as informal workspaces. Tampa Bay's cost of living, lifestyle, and lack of state income tax have made it a popular destination for remote workers earning coastal-city salaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What about nursing jobs specifically?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Tampa Bay has constant demand for nurses at every level — RN, LPN, ARNP. BayCare, AdventHealth, Tampa General, and Moffitt Cancer Center are always hiring. Travel nursing agencies also operate here. Salaries are competitive for Florida, though lower than Northeast or West Coast markets. The trade-off is no state income tax and lower cost of living."}},{"@type":"Question","na